ere is how I am going to do this.<br>
<br>
I am going to look for a replacement for Dragon Raids.  Leading both, in the long run, would be extremely stressful, and I feel like I would end up neglecting my own guild.  Right now, I know of not many qualified people that would be interested in taking over dragon raids.  There are several people that I would be willing to entrust this to, but most of those I do not feel would want to take over those duties. If you feel that you would like to take over the Dragon Leadership, send me a tell in game or shoot me an email (logan@soulsofthevaliant.org).  <br>
<br>
Here is what I am looking for as far as a qualified individual.  First of all, I am looking for someone that has the scheduling available to do this, which means that you must have the ability to be able to get on by 8pm EST (KGC rules dictate that a guild must start gathering by this point) any given night to lead a raid.  Of course vacation away, and things like that can be excused, but for the most you need to be able to get on to lead these things.  You need to be knowledgeable about tactics, and have experience with these dragons.  I don't mean you have to have participated in 10+ dragon raids, one of each is fine.  But reading up on dragons and actually going on a raid are two seperate things.  Also previous experience leading multigroup raids (guild mini raids or anything of that nature is fine) is preferred.  You really should be a Guild Leader or a Guild officer, as you really need a guild behind you to help you with it, though that is not a requirement.  Also Lastly (and in my opinion most importantly) you must have confidence in yourself to lead.  This sounds like a given, but it cannot be stressed enough.  You have to step in and take charge of 30-60 individuals, and if you are hesitating people will take advantage of it.  You need to be able to put down your foot and say &quot;This is how it IS going to be.  Period.&quot;.  If you don't have confidence in your own leadership you cannot do this.  This is not to say you must be perfect, after all I have made many mistakes, but you have to have that strong will, determination, and confidence to make sure people will follow you.  Those things are to me what would be the perfect candidate, but you do not have to match all the criterion.  Send me a tell if you are interested, and we can talk.<br>
<br>
Also, note that I am leveling past 52 (Actually already have hit 53), which means that I will not be able to actually engage dragons.  Until I find a suitable replacement I will continue to lead the dragon raids, but as a general instead of a raider.  If anyone has any questions about this feel free to send me an email, or to send me a tell in game.<br>
